b Spanish spoken in home 
</P>
<P>
c Spanish-surname population 
</P>
<P>
d Spanish-origin population (self-identification) 
</P>
<P>
The definitions of Latinos used by the U.S. Census has varied historically 
since 1860, when "Mexican foreign born" was first used. 
</P>
