DIGEST: NORWALK; 
</P>
<P>
COLLEGE SEEKS FEDERAL GRANT FOR DRUG PREVENTION PROJECT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Cerritos College will apply for a federal grant of nearly $150,000 to help with 
a campus drug prevention program. The college Board of Trustees gave unanimous 
approval Tuesday to an application requesting the money from the U.S. 
Department of Education. 
</P>
<P>
The money would be used to start an education and drug prevention program at 
the 18,000-student school in Norwalk. The college would contribute more than 
$230,000 to the project. 
</P>
<P>
The program would include drug prevention counseling for faculty and students 
and information on drug prevention throughout the curriculum. 
</P>
<P>
"We hope to develop a program to prevent drug use among students and teachers. 
We hope we can impact generations of students, parents and grandparents," said 
Jan Dennis-Rounds, college administrative dean of educational support services. 
</P>
</TEXT>
