WESTSIDE DIGEST: CULVER CITY; 
</P>
<P>
CENTER PRESENTS TEEN VIDEO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Cope III Video Productions, a program of the Didi Hirsch Community Mental 
Health Center, will show, "Help, I Need Somebody," a video about teen-age 
problems and solutions. 
</P>
<P>
The video was written, performed and produced by Culver City High School 
students involved in a three-month substance abuse prevention program, 
sponsored by the Los Angeles County Office of Alcohol Programs. 
</P>
<P>
The premiere showing will be April 6 from 7 to 9 p.m. at the center, 4760 S. 
Sepulveda Blvd. Admission is free. The audience will have a chance to meet the 
students involved in producing the video. 
</P>
<P>
For more information, call (213) 390-6612, Ext. 438. 
</P>
</TEXT>
