<HEADLINE>
<P>
RECALLING 'FORGOTTEN GENOCIDE' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"Recalling 'Forgotten Genocide,' " Feb. 9, we were treated to the half truths 
and historical revisions propounded by Justin McCarthy. McCarthy's livelihood 
depends on Turkey, whose propaganda machine he has become. 
</P>
<P>
In addition, a large amount of space was dedicated to parroting Turkish 
government propaganda regarding the Armenian genocide. 
</P>
<P>
If the point of the article was not our recently published handbook on the 
genocide but rather issues arising from the genocide, then, at the very least, 
a scholar of good repute should have been approached. 
</P>
<P>
GAREN YEGPARIAN 
</P>
<P>
Glendale 
</P>
<P>
Yegparian is executive director of the Western region of the Armenian National 
Committee. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA032389-0085 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 34501 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
March 23, 1989, Thursday, Home Edition 
