<P>
SPORTS ET CETERA: POINT LOMA NAZARENE BREEZES TO 10-3 VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Point Loma Nazarene College scored seven runs in the fourth inning, then 
coasted to a 10-3 victory over George Fox College (11-7) in a nonconference 
game at Point Loma. Craig Gastineau hit a two-run homer to get things started 
in the fourth for the Crusaders (11-11). Tom Martin (2-1) pitched six innings 
and got the victory. 
</P>
<P>
SWIMMING 
</P>
<P>
Three San Diego swimmers placed in the top 10 at the United States Swimming 
national championships in Chapel Hill, N.C. 
</P>
<P>
For Swim San Diego, Mike Picotte placed fourth in the men's 200 freestyle in 
1:38.02. Heartland Swim Assn.'s Matt Buckley was fourth in the men's 1,000 
freestyle in 9:08.94 and Michelle Butcher placed seventh in the women's 1,650 
freestyle in 16:24.94. 
</P>
<P>
MEN'S TENNIS 
</P>
<P>
The University of San Diego defeated San Jose State, 5-1, in a nonconference 
match in San Jose. Dave Stewart, Chris Toomey, Dan Mattera, J.R. Edwards and 
Rick Matheson won in singles for the No. 21-ranked Toreros (18-3). 
</P>
<P>
San Diego State split its singles matches but lost two of three doubles matches 
and lost to Weber State, 5-4, in the UC Irvine tournament. For SDSU (5-12), Joe 
McDonough, Woody Yocam and Bill Kearsley won in singles. The Yocam-Kearsley 
team won in doubles. Weber State is 9-5. 
</P>
<P>
WOMEN'S TENNIS 
</P>
<P>
San Diego State lost just one set to South Carolina (3-11) and defeated the 
Gamecocks, 5-0, in a nonconference match in Columbia, S.C. Sondra Mitchell, 
Kristin Hill, Jessica Buss, Susan Hawke and Eva Olivarez won for the 
18th-ranked Aztecs (10-6). 
</P>
