<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO INDUSTRY NOTES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Vista Group, a New Canaan, Conn.-based venture capital firm with $338 million 
invested in 110 companies worldwide, has opened a Western regional office in 
Del Mar. 
</P>
<P>
Of the companies in Vista Group's portfolio, about 31 are headquartered in 
California and three in San Diego: Springtime, Scientific Computer Systems and 
Computer Accessories. 
</P>
<P>
Spokeswoman Mary Lou Brennan said the firm opened the Del Mar office to be 
close to its several Southern California-based investments. Managers of the Del 
Mar office will be John F. Tomlin and Robert C. Fleming. 
</P>
<P>
"Vista looks forward to financing entrepreneurial ventures in the (San Diego) 
region," said Gerald Bay, the firm's managing general partner. 
</P>
<P>
Vista Group now manages eight separate investment funds from mainly 
institutional investors including British Petroleum, General Electric, Mutual 
of New York and Cigna, North American Phillips and Mitsui &amp; Co. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA032389-0141 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 34641 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
March 23, 1989, Thursday, Orange County Edition 
