<P>
SCHOOL BOARD RAISES FEES FOR DEVELOPERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Board of Education has approved a slight increase in fees that the Los 
Angeles Unified School District can impose on developers for school 
construction. 
</P>
<P>
The increase will generate an additional $1.5 million for school construction, 
a district report said. 
</P>
<P>
Effective June 1, fees on residential development will rise from $1.53 to $1.56 
per square foot, while commercial development fees will increase from 25 cents 
to 26 cents per square foot. 
</P>
<P>
State law requires districts to levy the fees in order to qualify for state 
school construction money. The state authorized the fee increase as an 
inflation adjustment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
