<P>
SUPERVISORS OK PLAN FOR CHILDREN'S COURT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Los Angeles County Board of Supervisors has adopted a plan to build a 
$52.3-million Children's Court and agreed to set aside $3.5 million to purchase 
a site in Monterey Park for the new facility. 
</P>
<P>
A 25-court children's facility will be built on the 4.17-acre site to 
accommodate a program in which judges decide whether children should be placed 
in foster care, as well as deciding on counseling and therapy. 
</P>
<P>
"This court will deal exclusively with cases involving abused, abandoned and 
neglected children -- youngsters who have been removed from their homes because 
of the situations in those environments," said Supervisor Ed Edelman. 
</P>
<P>
The project cost is $7.2 million higher than estimates, which officials blamed 
on inflation and increases in architectural and engineering requirements. 
</P>
</TEXT>
