<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: TOURISM / LEISURE TIME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Mary Ann Galante, Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Anaheim Hilton and Towers has appointed a specialist in guest services for 
Japanese visitors. 
</P>
<P>
Sue Moriyasu has been added as manager of Japanese guest services to welcome 
Japanese patrons and help communications between them and the hotel staff 
members, said Glenn A. Hale, general manager at the hotel. 
</P>
<P>
Moriyasu will meet tour groups and coordinate baggage delivery, wake-up calls, 
mail service, foreign exchange and meals for groups and individual travelers 
from Japan. 
</P>
<P>
Moriyasu was concierge at the Westin Bonaventure Hotel in Los Angeles, where 
she aided Japanese patrons with translation, travel arrangements and restaurant 
reservations. 
</P>
<P>
"We hope this new position will affirm our commitment to the comfort and 
hospitality of this important segment of the leisure market," Hale said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
