<HEADLINE>
<P>
THERE'S A PLACE FOR A FAMILIAR FACE ALONG 600-FOOT MURAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"The Tell," a 600-foot-long mural made of 40,000 photographs, will be put up 
along Laguna Canyon Road in Laguna Beach on May 1 to celebrate the 150th 
anniversary of photography's birth and the Orange County Centennial -- but only 
if project director Mark Chamberlain can collect 30,000 snapshots from county 
residents from now to April 10. 
</P>
<P>
Photos of anything at all will do, in either color or black and white. They 
cannot be returned. Send them to BC Space, 235 Forest Ave., Laguna Beach, 
Calif. 92651. 
</P>
<P>
Or come to a "Print Party" at the gallery April 1 from 7 to 10 p.m. Admission 
will be five or more photos. Prizes will be awarded for the most photos 
contributed. Information: (714) 497-1880. 
</P>
</TEXT>
