<HEADLINE>
<P>
EASY CAKE FOR CHILDREN TO MAKE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
This easy-to-make cocoa cake is a good recipe to use to introduce children to 
the fun of baking. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
LICKITY SPLIT COCOA CAKE 
</P>
<P>
1 1/2 cups flour 
</P>
<P>
1 cup sugar 
</P>
<P>
1/4 cup cocoa 
</P>
<P>
1 teaspoon baking soda 
</P>
<P>
1/2 teaspoon salt 
</P>
<P>
1 cup water 
</P>
<P>
6 tablespoons oil 
</P>
<P>
1 tablespoon vinegar 
</P>
<P>
1 teaspoon vanilla 
</P>
<P>
2 tablespoons powdered sugar 
</P>
<P>
Combine flour, sugar, cocoa, soda and salt. Add water, oil, vinegar and vanilla 
and stir just until batter is smooth and well blended. Pour into greased and 
floured 9-inch layer cake pan or 8-inch square pan. 
</P>
<P>
Bake at 350 degrees 35 to 40 minutes or until cake tester inserted in center 
comes out clean. Cool. Dust with powdered sugar. Makes 9 servings. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Recipe 
</P>
</TYPE>
