<HEADLINE>
<P>
CHARITY SCORECARD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Heady experience -- Florist Jim Delamore's headdress, "Brazil Oba Oba," modeled 
by Mary Latta, took the Sweepstakes prize on Saturday night at the annual Bal 
Masque sponsored by Damas de Caridad at the Disneyland Hotel. Proceeds of more 
than $60,000 will go to St. Jude Hospital in Fullerton. Ardie Davis was 
chairwoman. 
</P>
<P>
The Arthritis Foundation Women's Auxiliary luncheon at the Irvine Marriott on 
March 14 raised $10,000. Proceeds will be used to help support the Orange 
County Branch of the foundation. Former UC Irvine Chancellor Daniel G. Aldrich 
was honored at the affair. Elaine Vafiadis was chairwoman. Aldrich was 
recipient of the foundation's annual STOP -- Salute to Outstanding Persons -- 
Award. He attended with his wife, Jean. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Florist Jim Delamore's headdress, "Brazil Oba Oba," modeled by Mary 
Latta. R. VERONICA DECKER 
</P>
