<HEADLINE>
<P>
'COLD WARRIORS' DRAW CRITICISM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
It was with a feeling of revulsion that I read the article "Regrouping in the 
Cold War" (Times, March 16). 
</P>
<P>
My disgust was caused, not by Times Staff Writer Mike Ward's journalistic 
style, but by the subject. How depressing it is to be reminded that there are 
among us radical groups such as the John Birch Society, members of which 
continue to embrace McCarthyism. 
</P>
<P>
Fortunately, the great majority of people in this country reject the kind of 
political depravity espoused by such organizations as the Birchers. The only 
redemption I find in the article is that I can offer it to my students as an 
example of what Samuel Johnson meant when he said: "Patriotism is the last 
refuge of the scoundrel." 
</P>
<P>
TIM KARAMITROS 
</P>
<P>
Sierra Madre 
</P>
</TEXT>
