<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DISTRICT: MONTEREY PARK; 
</P>
<P>
TOUR BUS SCHEDULE OKD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Tour bus operators and city officials have reached an informal agreement as 
part of a plan to eliminate traffic congestion from buses and passengers 
crowding city streets. 
</P>
<P>
City officials met with the half-dozen major tour bus companies that operate 
vacation tours originating in Monterey Park and traveling throughout the 
Southwest and California. 
</P>
<P>
The bus companies agreed to load and unload on off-street locations and to 
separate these spots as much as possible. The operators also agreed to have 
buses depart before 8:30 a.m. and to return to Monterey Park on staggered 
schedules. 
</P>
<P>
"The problem was that 10 to 12 buses would be in one place, loading up on a 
Saturday morning, blocking visibility and with pedestrians running all over the 
street to get to a bus," said Assistant City Manager Stan Soo-Hoo. 
</P>
<P>
"The idea was to address the problem and not overreact in a police kind of 
way." Bus operators last year complained that city officials had arbitrarily 
issued citations to buses that had allegedly committed zoning violations by 
improper parking on city streets. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
