NATION; 
</P>
<P>
JET TAKES OFF FROM WRONG RUNWAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
GRAPEVINE, Tex. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An American Airlines jet took off from the wrong runway in Houston today and 
struck a metal barricade, but continued to a safe landing at Dallas-Fort Worth 
International Airport, federal officials said. 
</P>
<P>
There were no injuries on Flight 508, which arrived on time at Dallas, its 
intended destination, the airline said. The Federal Aviation Administration 
said more than 90 people were on board. The MD-80 jet mistakenly took off from 
a runway undergoing construction at Houston's Hobby Airport and marked for use 
by light planes only, said Geraldine Cook, spokeswoman for the FAA's regional 
office in Fort Worth. 
</P>
