<HEADLINE>
<P>
IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
NO DECISION ON PETE ROSE TODAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A spokesman for Baseball Commissioner Peter Ueberroth said there will be no 
announcement today on the results of an inquiry into allegations of gambling by 
Reds Manager Pete Rose. 
</P>
<P>
Jim Small, spokesman in the commissioner's office, told the Associated Press 
today that the investigation is not completed. "There will be no announcement 
today. Reports to the contrary, we will have nothing to say today. The 
investigation is still continuing." 
</P>
<P>
Rose has refused to discuss allegations that have linked him with gambling and 
that could jeopardize his future in baseball. One of the allegations reported 
under investigation is that Rose may have bet on baseball, possibly his own 
team. (Story, Part III, Page 1.) 
</P>
<P>
If proven true, Rose would be suspended or even banned for life. 
</P>
</TEXT>
